available_zones.description: List of available zones in region

instances_details.description: List of all details for compute instances

instances_self_links.description: List of self-links for compute instances

access_config.description: Access configurations, i.e. IPs via which the VM instance can be accessed via the Internet.

instance_template.description: Instance template self_link used to create compute instances

network.description: Network to deploy to. Only one of network or subnetwork should be specified.

num_instances.description: Number of instances to create. This value is ignored if static_ips is provided.

region.description: Region where the instances should be created.

static_ips.description: List of static IPs for VM instances

subnetwork.description: Subnet to deploy to. Only one of network or subnetwork should be specified.

subnetwork_project.description: The project that subnetwork belongs to

tags.description: Tags that will be associated with instance(s)

access_config.description: Access configurations, i.e. IPs via which the VM instance can be accessed via the Internet.

additional_disks.description: List of maps of additional disks. See https://www.terraform.io/docs/providers/google/r/compute_instance_template.html#disk_name

additional_networks.description: Additional network interface details for GCE, if any.

alias_ip_range.description:
An array of alias IP ranges for this network interface. Can only be specified for network interfaces on subnet-mode networks.
ip_cidr_range: The IP CIDR range represented by this alias IP range. This IP CIDR range must belong to the specified subnetwork and cannot contain IP addresses reserved by system or used by other network interfaces. At the time of writing only a netmask (e.g. /24) may be supplied, with a CIDR format resulting in an API error.
subnetwork_range_name: The subnetwork secondary range name specifying the secondary range from which to allocate the IP CIDR range for this alias IP range. If left unspecified, the primary range of the subnetwork will be used.

auto_delete.description: Whether or not the boot disk should be auto-deleted

can_ip_forward.description: Enable IP forwarding, for NAT instances for example

disk_encryption_key.description: The id of the encryption key that is stored in Google Cloud KMS to use to encrypt all the disks on this instance

disk_labels.description: Labels to be assigned to boot disk, provided as a map

disk_type.description: Boot disk type, can be either pd-ssd, local-ssd, or pd-standard

enable_confidential_vm.description: Whether to enable the Confidential VM configuration on the instance. Note that the instance image must support Confidential VMs. See https://cloud.google.com/compute/docs/images

enable_shielded_vm.description: Whether to enable the Shielded VM configuration on the instance. Note that the instance image must support Shielded VMs. See https://cloud.google.com/compute/docs/images

gpu.description: GPU information. Type and count of GPU to attach to the instance template. See https://cloud.google.com/compute/docs/gpus more details

machine_type.description: Machine type to create, e.g. n1-standard-1

min_cpu_platform.description: Specifies a minimum CPU platform. Applicable values are the friendly names of CPU platforms, such as Intel Haswell or Intel Skylake. See the complete list: https://cloud.google.com/compute/docs/instances/specify-min-cpu-platform

name_prefix.description: Name prefix for the instance template

network.description: The name or self_link of the network to attach this interface to. Use network attribute for Legacy or Auto subnetted networks and subnetwork for custom subnetted networks.

network_ip.description: Private IP address to assign to the instance if desired.

preemptible.description: Allow the instance to be preempted

region.description: Region where the instance template should be created.

service_account.description: Service account to attach to the instance. See https://www.terraform.io/docs/providers/google/r/compute_instance_template.html#service_account.

shielded_instance_config.description: Not used unless enable_shielded_vm is true. Shielded VM configuration for the instance.

source_image.description: Source disk image. If neither source_image nor source_image_family is specified, defaults to the latest public CentOS image.

source_image_family.description: Source image family. If neither source_image nor source_image_family is specified, defaults to the latest public CentOS image.

source_image_project.description: Project where the source image comes from. The default project contains CentOS images.

startup_script.description: User startup script to run when instances spin up

subnetwork.description: The name of the subnetwork to attach this interface to. The subnetwork must exist in the same region this instance will be created in. Either network or subnetwork must be provided.

subnetwork_project.description: The ID of the project in which the subnetwork belongs. If it is not provided, the provider project is used.

tags.description: Network tags, provided as a list

business_code.description: The code that describes which business unit owns the project

environment.description: The environment the single project belongs to

folder_id.description: The folder id where project will be created

machine_type.description: Machine type to create, e.g. n1-standard-1

projectId.description: The folder id where project will be created

project_suffix.description: The name of the GCP project. Max 16 characters with 3 character business unit code.

region.description: The GCP region to create and test resources in

service_account.description: Service account to attach to the instance. See https://www.terraform.io/docs/providers/google/r/compute_instance_template.html#service_account.

vpc_type.description: The type of VPC to attach the project to. Possible options are base or restricted.
